time required: 30 minutes
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/mushroom-panzanella-salad-572322dbfd2cb93c648b4567
---

Pre-heat your #oven{} to 210 degrees. Cut the @ciabatta{1} into 1cm cubes, toss in
@olive oil{4%tbsp}, lay on a #baking tray{} and pop in your oven for
~{10-15%minutes} until golden brown and crisp. When ready, remove your croutons
from your oven, sprinkle with a @salt{pinch} and set aside to cool.

> Keep an eye on your croutons and check them after 8 mins to make sure they
> aren't burning!

In the meantime, cut the @red onion{1} in half through the root, peel and slice
thinly into half moon shapes. Put @olive oil{2%tbsp} in a #saucepan{} on
medium-low heat and add the onions. Cook for ~{10%minutes}, then add the
@balsamic vinegar{1}, turn the heat to low, put the #lid{} on and cook for a
further ~{10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, cut the @portobello mushrooms{1} into 1cm slices and chop each
@vine tomatoes{2} into eight wedges.

Put the tomatoes into a #bowl{} and squeeze over half the @lemon{1/2} juice,
@salt{1/4%tsp} and a good grind of @ground black pepper{}. Drizzle over
@olive oil{1%tbsp} and leave to the side.

Put @butter{1%tbsp}(if you have some) or @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #frying pan{}
on medium-high heat and add the mushroom slices. Sprinkle over @salt{1/4%tsp}
and a good grind of @ground black pepper{}. Cook for ~{4-5%minutes} until the
mushrooms are browned, then remove the pan from the heat.

> If your pan is quite small, do this in batches to avoid stewing the
> mushrooms.

While the mushrooms are cooking tear up the @mozzarella{1} and put three-quarters
of it into the bowl with the tomatoes.

When everything is ready add the @wild rocket{1} to the bowl as well, along with
your caramelised onion and cooked mushrooms. Tear in half of the
@basil{1/2}, throw in three quarters of your croutons and squeeze over the
rest of the lemon juice. Toss everything together and check the seasoning.
Sprinkle in a little more salt and pepper if you need to.

Serve your panzanella in #bowls{}, with the rest of the mozzarella and croutons
on top and tear over the remaining basil. Enjoy!